{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Nq9tRmbUx6AgAYYzkCzsHh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All users authenticate successfully and the cluster remains healthy. Here's what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** `report-user` was added to a separate secret (`user-provided-file-realm`) instead of the `es-file-realm-aggregate` secret that the cluster reads. Additionally, the statefulset wasn't mounting any file-realm secret at all, so no file-realm users could authenticate.\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n\n1. **Merged users** — combined `report-user` credentials from `user-provided-file-realm` into `es-file-realm-aggregate` (which already held `ops-user`)\n\n2. **Patched the statefulset** — added a `file-realm` volume backed by `es-file-realm-aggregate` and mounted `users` and `users_roles` at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users` and `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users_roles` — the paths ES reads by default for the file realm\n\n3. **Created the `read` role** — `read` is not a built-in role in ES 7.17.9 (unlike other versions), so `report-user`'s role assignment resolved to nothing; created it via the Security API with index-level read privileges\n\n4. **Seeded `app-data` index** — the precondition couldn't seed it earlier (ops-user wasn't auth'd yet); created it now so report-user has data to read"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":625,"cache_read_input_tokens":55936,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":625},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2e08a919-b11e-4bc0-bd98-46ab2b5deb66","uuid":"ca9baeb7-91ea-4339-a97b-3a949f23fc3c","request_id":"req_011CcLxd1nZyazrDudCFES5N"}
